		<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Both Air Manager &amp; Air Player have support for multiple Arduino devices.<br />
You are able to use Air Manager or Air Player to drive LED's, Buttons, Switches, Rotary encoders etc. through the Arduino.
</p><p>Within Air Manager you will find the installer that will flash your Arduino, to make it possible to communicate with Air Manager or Air Player automatically using an USB connection.
</p>
<div style="background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.1); border: solid thin grey; padding: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center;&#125;&#125;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Warning.png" class="image" title="Info"><img alt="Info" src="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/18px-Warning.png" decoding="async" width="18" height="18" srcset="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/27px-Warning.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/36px-Warning.png 2x" /></a> <span style="margin-top:-0px; padding-left:16px; display:block;">Arduino MEGA 2560 (up to REV 3), Uno (up to REV 3), Micro, Leonardo and Nano are supported, other Arduino models will not work.</span></div>
<p><br />
</p>
